      "steps": [],
      "id": "math/60.18"
    },
    {
      "question": "<p>On a la fonction lin&eacute;aire : <u><span style=\"font-size: 15pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">f(</span><span style=\"font-size: 15pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: 'Cambria Math', serif;\">𝑥</span><span style=\"font-size: 15pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">) = 2</span></u><span style=\"font-size: 15pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: 'Cambria Math', serif;\"><u>𝑥</u>.</span></p>\n<p>La droite passe-t-elle par <u>le point (2 ; 2)</u> ?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "explain": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 15.0pt; font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; color: black;\">Si </span><span style=\"font-size: 15.0pt; font-family: 'Cambria Math',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Cambria Math'; color: black;\">𝑥</span><span style=\"font-size: 15.0pt; font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; color: black;\"> = 2, alors f(2) = 2&times;2 = 4. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 15.0pt; font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; color: black;\">Donc, <u>la droite ne passe pas par le point (2 ; 2)</u>.</span></p>",
      "choices": [
